Bakefile is used to generate makefiles. The bakefile is the standard build script generator for this project since Sept. 2019.

Each bakefile is referenced from a single script under the project/ directory.

Each file is referenced from the parent directory.

On the command-line, if you are in the same directory as the bakefiles themselves you are in the wrong directory.

In the example directory tree below, this file is in the directory noted with an *.

Go up one level (e.g.  cd ..)

Then run the script create_make.sh as follows: ./create_make.sh

├── app.css
├── * bakefiles
│   ├── prog_newsdownld.bkl
│   ├── prog_newsreader.bkl
│   └── prog_rss_io_test.bkl
├── buildscripts
│   ├── build_newsdownld.mk
│   ├── build_newsdownld.sh
│   ├── build_newsreader.mk
│   ├── build_newsreader.sh
│   ├── build_rss_io_test.mk
│   └── build_rss_io_test.sh
├── create_make.sh
├── format_code.sh
├── rss.db
├── run_newsdownld.sh
├── run_newsreader.sh
├── run_rss_io_test.sh
├── update_rss_db_use_offline_xml.sh
├── valgrind_checks
│   ├── newsreader_leakcheck_full.sh
│   └── newsreader_leakcheck_full.suppr
└── xfer
    ├── exchange_code_and_exe.sh
    ├── get_dev_env_output.sh
    └── send_code_to_vm.sh

